1
00:00:03,504 --> 00:00:04,438
AUGUST 2015

2
00:00:04,505 --> 00:00:05,506
<i>"Ms. Suenaga.</i>

3
00:00:06,907 --> 00:00:07,775
<i>Back then</i>

4
00:00:08,776 --> 00:00:10,511
<i>I was a little crazy.</i>

5
00:00:12,279 --> 00:00:13,981
<i>I'd get irritated for no reason,</i>

6
00:00:15,149 --> 00:00:16,150
<i>and lose control.</i>

7
00:00:17,385 --> 00:00:21,555
<i>To a point where I couldn't see</i>
<i>myself or my surroundings.</i>

8
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:25,659
<i>That's how much…</i>

9
00:00:28,062 --> 00:00:29,063
<i>I loved you."</i>

10
00:00:31,465 --> 00:00:32,967
<i>I'll ask again.</i>

11
00:00:33,034 --> 00:00:34,001
Are you sure?

12
00:00:35,169 --> 00:00:36,003
At this rate…

13
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:39,073
He's in middle school.

14
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:40,174
Ms. Suenaga!

15
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:46,947
Ms. Suenaga!

16
00:00:48,682 --> 00:00:49,750
Ms. Suenaga!

17
00:00:58,793 --> 00:01:00,094
<i>I'm sorry, Mom.</i>

18
00:01:01,195 --> 00:01:03,564
<i>I fell in love with a student.</i>

19
00:01:04,165 --> 00:01:06,033
APRIL 2015

20
00:01:07,034 --> 00:01:09,470
OPENING CEREMONY

21
00:01:10,938 --> 00:01:12,573
One minute of silence.

22
00:01:20,548 --> 00:01:23,884
HIJIRI SUENAGA

23
00:01:27,321 --> 00:01:28,522
I had no idea.

24
00:01:29,390 --> 00:01:30,658
One year ago today,

25
00:01:31,158 --> 00:01:35,563
a worker died when a meteor
struck them from the sky.

26
00:01:35,629 --> 00:01:38,499
I had heard that the stars
are pretty in Koboshidaira.

27
00:01:38,566 --> 00:01:41,135
Did you all pray--

28
00:01:41,202 --> 00:01:42,403
Ms. Suenaga!

29
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:43,737
Yes, um…

30
00:01:43,804 --> 00:01:44,872
CLASS ONE SEATING CHART

31
00:01:44,939 --> 00:01:46,307
-Ms. Iwasaki.
-We lied.

32
00:01:46,907 --> 00:01:47,575
What?

33
00:01:47,641 --> 00:01:50,411
While a worker did collapse
on school grounds,

34
00:01:51,545 --> 00:01:53,180
you can see he's fine.

35
00:01:53,247 --> 00:01:54,081
Huh?

36
00:01:55,082 --> 00:01:58,352
Then what about a NASA researcher
coming every year?

37
00:01:58,419 --> 00:01:59,420
Not true.

38
00:01:59,487 --> 00:02:00,354
Not true?

39
00:02:01,489 --> 00:02:06,527
Huh? Then what about the huge meteor
shower that happens every 100 years?

40
00:02:06,594 --> 00:02:08,562
-And it's this year--
-Not true either.

41
00:02:08,629 --> 00:02:12,266
Just so you know,
I came up with all those stories!

42
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:15,703
-Yay!
-Sit down.

43
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:17,972
-All lies.
-Sit down.

44
00:02:20,007 --> 00:02:21,909
Junichiro Kokonoe.

45
00:02:21,976 --> 00:02:22,977
Yes?

46
00:02:29,450 --> 00:02:31,452
Those lies are inappropriate.

47
00:02:31,986 --> 00:02:34,188
-You'll need to be reprimanded.
-Huh?

48
00:02:34,255 --> 00:02:36,857
I'm sending you to social skill training.

49
00:02:37,391 --> 00:02:39,026
See me after school.

50
00:02:39,093 --> 00:02:41,095
-Huh? For real?
-No, I'm kidding.

51
00:02:45,766 --> 00:02:47,501
-What?
-Kuroiwa!

52
00:02:48,002 --> 00:02:49,103
What're you doing?

53
00:02:54,341 --> 00:02:55,209
You okay?

54
00:03:06,587 --> 00:03:07,421
Huh?

55
00:03:08,389 --> 00:03:09,557
Did you hit your head?

56
00:03:09,623 --> 00:03:11,091
-Ms. Suenaga.
-Hmm?

57
00:03:11,158 --> 00:03:13,294
He's always like this.

58
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:24,672
-How did you greet them?
-Reminds me of my practical training days.

59
00:03:24,738 --> 00:03:28,576
Out of all the trainees I looked after
your efforts lacked the most motion.

60
00:03:28,642 --> 00:03:29,877
What?

61
00:03:29,944 --> 00:03:31,278
Go on, show me.

62
00:03:35,449 --> 00:03:38,285
-Nice to meet you, I'm Hijiri Suenaga.
-A bit stiff.

63
00:03:38,352 --> 00:03:40,354
After graduating university in Tokyo,

64
00:03:40,421 --> 00:03:44,191
I worked for two years as a part-time
teacher at grade and middle schools.

65
00:03:44,258 --> 00:03:45,492
Yeah.

66
00:03:45,559 --> 00:03:47,228
Ms. Chizuru, are you listening?

67
00:03:47,294 --> 00:03:48,862
Yes, I'm listening.

68
00:03:48,929 --> 00:03:50,564
You're doing a good job.

69
00:03:51,131 --> 00:03:54,435
Abandoning your love life to focus
on teaching was worth it.

70
00:03:54,501 --> 00:03:55,736
I haven't.

71
00:03:55,803 --> 00:03:58,072
I'm long-distance with Shotaro.

72
00:03:58,138 --> 00:04:01,508
He's in Osaka, and you're
in the Kanagawa sticks.

73
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:03,143
You should've followed him.

74
00:04:03,877 --> 00:04:07,414
It's not like he asked me to.

75
00:04:07,481 --> 00:04:12,253
I mean, you've been dating
for three years, and no ring yet?

76
00:04:12,319 --> 00:04:14,688
Maybe he's not ready to settle down.

77
00:04:18,826 --> 00:04:19,994
But it was my dream.

78
00:04:21,362 --> 00:04:25,232
To have my own homeroom class
despite all the drawbacks

79
00:04:25,299 --> 00:04:28,869
of being a young, unmarried woman.

80
00:04:30,371 --> 00:04:33,107
It may not seem like it,
but I'm super motivated.

81
00:04:33,173 --> 00:04:33,974
Yup!

82
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:35,209
Cheers.

83
00:04:41,582 --> 00:04:43,484
You're inappropriate.

84
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:44,451
What?

85
00:04:44,518 --> 00:04:46,754
That's what they're saying.

86
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:48,856
-Already.
-That's Old Lady Shioya.

87
00:04:48,922 --> 00:04:50,190
Suenaga's in trouble.

88
00:04:50,257 --> 00:04:52,226
-How stupid!
-There's the Internet now.

89
00:04:52,293 --> 00:04:55,496
Cute, not cute, lame.

90
00:04:55,562 --> 00:04:59,400
They may say that,
but always be dignified,

91
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:01,568
and do not show any weakness.

92
00:05:02,069 --> 00:05:02,736
Yes, ma'am.

93
00:05:02,803 --> 00:05:06,106
Right now, population decline is an issue.

94
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,641
Did you know that?

95
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:13,947
Every year, 500 schools close
due to the declining population.

96
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:19,653
Teachers must protect
the school's reputation at all cost.

97
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:21,422
Understood.

98
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:23,924
How are the third years, Ms. Suenaga?

99
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:25,893
They're all hardworking.

100
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:27,728
They only look hardworking.

101
00:05:27,795 --> 00:05:30,631
That's your school account.

102
00:05:30,698 --> 00:05:35,669
You can log in here to place
lunch orders and contact parents.

103
00:05:35,736 --> 00:05:36,870
Thank you!

104
00:05:36,937 --> 00:05:41,208
Normally, a new teacher like you wouldn't

105
00:05:41,275 --> 00:05:45,045
be left to handle third years like this.

106
00:05:45,112 --> 00:05:47,514
Since your predecessor
is on maternity leave…

107
00:05:47,581 --> 00:05:50,684
-I have high hopes though.
-Oh my!

108
00:05:50,751 --> 00:05:55,789
Ms. Suenaga's essay was full of passion
and came from the heart.

109
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:56,757
Impressive!

110
00:05:56,824 --> 00:05:59,159
And you seem tough.

111
00:05:59,226 --> 00:06:00,060
Huh?

112
00:06:00,561 --> 00:06:01,695
Good luck.

113
00:06:02,196 --> 00:06:03,197
Okay.

114
00:06:03,263 --> 00:06:04,598
A minute of silence!

115
00:06:04,665 --> 00:06:06,400
So lame.

116
00:06:07,401 --> 00:06:09,770
-Suenaga is so wily.
-For sure.

117
00:06:09,837 --> 00:06:12,172
She acts like she doesn't wear makeup.

118
00:06:12,239 --> 00:06:14,208
The guys like her. Right?

119
00:06:14,274 --> 00:06:15,342
What?

120
00:06:15,409 --> 00:06:17,010
Don't you think Hijiri's cute?

121
00:06:18,212 --> 00:06:19,546
Not really.

122
00:06:19,613 --> 00:06:21,882
Wow! A total shutdown!

123
00:06:21,949 --> 00:06:23,317
That's Kuroiwa for you.

124
00:06:23,384 --> 00:06:26,387
Ever the insensitive,
non-conformist too cool for everyone.

125
00:06:28,956 --> 00:06:29,990
Come on, let's go.

126
00:06:30,657 --> 00:06:32,659
-Bye.
-Goodbye.

127
00:06:33,193 --> 00:06:35,429
-I'm off then.
-Have a good one.

128
00:06:37,197 --> 00:06:39,500
<i>Can you talk tonight?</i>

129
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:40,367
OSAKA

130
00:06:40,434 --> 00:06:42,002
HIJIRI

131
00:06:44,104 --> 00:06:45,539
You're getting sent out.

132
00:06:45,606 --> 00:06:46,774
What?

133
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,208
That's our new leader.

134
00:06:48,275 --> 00:06:50,210
Haraguchi from the New York office.

135
00:06:51,044 --> 00:06:54,014
She's a real career woman
with a short fuse.

136
00:06:54,882 --> 00:06:56,550
She should lighten up.

137
00:07:00,187 --> 00:07:02,189
-Ms. Kasuya!
-Coming.

138
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,495
Gonna grab some food.

139
00:07:09,229 --> 00:07:10,664
I'm stepping out.

140
00:07:10,731 --> 00:07:13,801
HIJIRI SUENAGA

141
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:10,457
Kuroiwa.

142
00:08:26,974 --> 00:08:27,808
Huh?

143
00:08:31,078 --> 00:08:32,713
So annoying.

144
00:08:32,779 --> 00:08:33,714
Hey Akira!

145
00:08:37,251 --> 00:08:38,886
Hold on, my precious son.

146
00:08:39,553 --> 00:08:42,289
I take it back, my not so precious son.

147
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:45,025
-Stop.
-You didn't eat my curry?

148
00:08:46,293 --> 00:08:48,595
If you're going to do this, I'm--

149
00:08:48,662 --> 00:08:51,331
I keep telling you I don't need food.

150
00:08:51,398 --> 00:08:53,066
Quite the opposite.

151
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:55,836
I'm going to make even more
elaborate dishes.

152
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:59,873
Something that requires
a lot of chopping or even shelling.

153
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:03,610
Time consuming food filled with my love
that I'll make every day

154
00:09:03,677 --> 00:09:05,846
that you'll throw out heartlessly.

155
00:09:05,913 --> 00:09:11,818
-Your ungratefulness will kill me.
-Shut up!

156
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:15,188
Oh, woe is me!

157
00:09:15,689 --> 00:09:17,224
I'll eat it.

158
00:09:18,058 --> 00:09:21,261
I'm jealous of Akira getting
to be a teenager.

159
00:09:21,328 --> 00:09:23,263
Listen, Joffe.

160
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:26,366
Being a teenager is no excuse.

161
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:28,835
He's just being rebellious.

162
00:09:30,003 --> 00:09:35,776
That cute round-eyed boy
is now a rebellious young man.

163
00:09:35,842 --> 00:09:39,112
I'm impressed you raised him
so well on your own.

164
00:09:39,179 --> 00:09:40,247
Boss!

165
00:09:41,181 --> 00:09:42,316
Hat's off!

166
00:09:42,382 --> 00:09:43,717
And thank you for the food.

167
00:09:44,952 --> 00:09:46,987
I'm worried about school.

168
00:09:47,054 --> 00:09:52,859
I want to talk with them, but his new
homeroom teacher is a young woman.

169
00:09:54,127 --> 00:09:59,499
According to the other moms,
she's rather cute, like a Russian doll.

170
00:09:59,566 --> 00:10:00,667
Good morning.

171
00:10:13,814 --> 00:10:14,915
We met yesterday.

172
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:18,619
I saw you buying a boxed lunch.

173
00:10:18,685 --> 00:10:20,220
Is your mom busy working?

174
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:26,026
Do you eat alone a lot?

175
00:10:28,629 --> 00:10:30,831
If you need to,
you can talk to me anytime.

176
00:10:30,897 --> 00:10:32,699
I want to be of help to you.

177
00:10:44,011 --> 00:10:45,379
I thought this yesterday,

178
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:48,048
but you have a pretty face.

179
00:10:50,751 --> 00:10:54,254
Please! You need to stop annoying me.

180
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,337
<i>Why did he hit me?</i>

181
00:11:11,673 --> 00:11:13,241
<i>Did I say something?</i>

182
00:11:15,410 --> 00:11:16,244
<i>Why?</i>

183
00:11:37,051 --> 00:11:38,486
OSAKA

184
00:11:38,553 --> 00:11:40,087
<i>Be vocal.</i>

185
00:11:40,154 --> 00:11:43,224
<i>And stand up for myself if a student</i>
<i>makes a comment.</i>

186
00:11:44,392 --> 00:11:46,294
<i>I follow these rules for myself.</i>

187
00:11:48,462 --> 00:11:52,266
<i>I even became the swim coach</i>
<i>when I said I swam as a kid.</i>

188
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,569
<i>Really?</i>

189
00:11:54,635 --> 00:11:58,773
Every day is hectic,
but all of my students seem nice.

190
00:12:04,412 --> 00:12:05,846
<i>-What's wrong?</i>
-Hmm?

191
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,448
Nothing.

192
00:12:09,050 --> 00:12:09,884
I'll do my best.

193
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,721
By the way,

194
00:12:14,956 --> 00:12:16,324
are you going this weekend?

195
00:12:16,991 --> 00:12:18,960
Yamamoto's transferring to London.

196
00:12:19,594 --> 00:12:20,695
<i>The farewell party?</i>

197
00:12:21,329 --> 00:12:22,697
<i>What about you?</i>

198
00:12:22,763 --> 00:12:25,199
I'll be in Tokyo for work, so I think so.

199
00:12:25,266 --> 00:12:26,267
Kawai.

200
00:12:26,334 --> 00:12:27,535
Yes?

201
00:12:27,602 --> 00:12:30,938
Go home if you're not going to work.

202
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:34,575
And the meeting was moved up an hour.

203
00:12:34,642 --> 00:12:35,977
<i>-Sorry, got to go.</i>
-Okay.

204
00:12:47,989 --> 00:12:49,724
I'm sorry, I thought I had time.

205
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,392
I said you could leave.

206
00:12:53,694 --> 00:12:58,132
You can cry about missing
your girlfriend at home.

207
00:12:58,199 --> 00:12:59,433
Is that from a song?

208
00:13:00,134 --> 00:13:02,069
You want me off the team?

209
00:13:02,136 --> 00:13:03,904
Today's web meeting is important.

210
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:05,773
Yes, it's big.

211
00:13:21,055 --> 00:13:22,823
What's going on?

212
00:13:23,758 --> 00:13:25,426
Why's her voice shaking so much?

213
00:13:26,761 --> 00:13:28,796
-She's always like this.
-Really?

214
00:13:28,863 --> 00:13:31,065
They call her Shaky Voice Haraguchi.

215
00:13:31,132 --> 00:13:35,002
But she never fails and even gets laughs.

216
00:13:42,877 --> 00:13:45,379
-Rumors say she's the boss's mistress.
-What?

217
00:13:45,446 --> 00:13:47,415
You go against her, you get exiled.

218
00:13:53,888 --> 00:13:54,989
Yamamoto.

219
00:13:55,056 --> 00:13:55,856
KENTA YAMAMOTO

220
00:13:58,559 --> 00:13:59,460
Mahiro?

221
00:14:04,298 --> 00:14:05,499
Kuroiwa.

222
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,335
AKIRA KUROIWA

223
00:14:09,136 --> 00:14:12,807
Parent teacher conference?
And it's this week?

224
00:14:13,941 --> 00:14:17,178
Why didn't you show this to me earlier?

225
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:20,047
Hey.

226
00:14:21,982 --> 00:14:24,719
-Did the school call you or anything?
-Huh?

227
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:26,954
Why?

228
00:14:29,323 --> 00:14:30,491
Hey.

229
00:14:30,558 --> 00:14:32,059
Hey, Akira!

230
00:14:34,895 --> 00:14:38,833
I'm going to talk to your teacher about
your teenage rebellion!

231
00:14:49,810 --> 00:14:51,712
KOSUKE SHIMAZAKI

232
00:14:53,647 --> 00:14:55,082
AS HIS FATHER…

233
00:14:55,149 --> 00:14:56,751
I WANT TO MEET AKIRA

234
00:15:05,226 --> 00:15:07,094
HIJIRI SUENAGA

235
00:15:09,230 --> 00:15:12,333
DEAR GUARDIAN, I THOUGHT YOU SHOULD KNOW.

236
00:15:13,434 --> 00:15:16,570
HIJIRI SUENAGA

237
00:15:18,072 --> 00:15:18,906
Maruoka.

238
00:15:22,943 --> 00:15:26,781
It looks like a strange code, doesn't it?

239
00:15:27,848 --> 00:15:29,750
<i>Hijiri hasn't told anyone</i>

240
00:15:30,651 --> 00:15:33,487
<i>that I slapped her yet.</i>

241
00:15:34,088 --> 00:15:34,922
<i>Why?</i>

242
00:15:34,989 --> 00:15:38,459
This is a poem by Chinese poet Du Fu.

243
00:15:38,526 --> 00:15:40,261
Page 23 in your text books.

244
00:15:40,327 --> 00:15:44,031
It was written about 1,250 years ago.

245
00:15:44,098 --> 00:15:45,499
But when you read it,

246
00:15:45,566 --> 00:15:49,970
the imagery of the scene expands
around you like a picture.

247
00:15:50,037 --> 00:15:52,506
Let's experience it together.

248
00:15:56,243 --> 00:15:59,013
"What color is Hijiri's bra?"

249
00:15:59,079 --> 00:16:00,448
Idiot!

250
00:16:01,048 --> 00:16:03,284
<i>Welcome Rain on a Spring Night.</i>

251
00:16:05,186 --> 00:16:10,191
Rejoicing a gentle spring shower
that begins during the night.

252
00:16:12,026 --> 00:16:14,028
"The good rain knows its season."

253
00:16:14,695 --> 00:16:16,964
Good rain knows of that time.

254
00:16:17,031 --> 00:16:19,400
-Time to find out!
-Spring has come.

255
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:20,835
In other words, it begins.

256
00:16:21,435 --> 00:16:24,138
"When spring arrives, it brings life.

257
00:16:25,206 --> 00:16:28,542
It follows the wind
secretly into the night--"

258
00:16:30,744 --> 00:16:32,046
Are you alright?

259
00:16:33,013 --> 00:16:34,949
You've got to be joking!

260
00:16:38,586 --> 00:16:40,621
Seriously, Kokonoe!

261
00:16:40,688 --> 00:16:42,990
Take out your phones right now!

262
00:16:44,225 --> 00:16:46,193
The whole class.

263
00:16:47,428 --> 00:16:48,662
Hurry up!

264
00:16:49,363 --> 00:16:51,999
This is what they were up to.

265
00:16:54,301 --> 00:16:55,870
