00:32:38,264 --> 00:32:39,799
Not yet.

540
00:32:42,769 --> 00:32:43,703
There she is.

541
00:32:43,770 --> 00:32:45,605
I'm so sorry.

542
00:32:45,672 --> 00:32:47,474
Everything's okay.

543
00:32:48,341 --> 00:32:49,576
This way.

544
00:33:00,553 --> 00:33:02,088
I'm sorry.

545
00:33:02,155 --> 00:33:03,657
I couldn't come right away.

546
00:33:03,723 --> 00:33:06,192
-I was out.
-It's okay.

547
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:10,430
We don't know how to apologize for this.

548
00:33:10,497 --> 00:33:11,331
It's nothing.

549
00:33:12,932 --> 00:33:14,300
APRIL 18TH, SATURDAY

550
00:33:16,403 --> 00:33:17,771
-I'm so glad.
-Ms. Shioya.

551
00:33:21,708 --> 00:33:22,742
Ms. Shioya.

552
00:33:26,479 --> 00:33:28,481
We were lucky.

553
00:33:28,548 --> 00:33:32,152
Kuroiwa put the fire out
and only suffered minor burns.

554
00:33:32,218 --> 00:33:35,989
The police won't be bringing any charges
as it didn't become a big incident.

555
00:33:36,589 --> 00:33:38,024
Just a stern warning.

556
00:33:38,558 --> 00:33:40,060
Thank you!

557
00:33:40,126 --> 00:33:42,295
-We're so sorry.
-I'm sorry.

558
00:33:44,564 --> 00:33:45,799
-You idiot!
-Sorry.

559
00:33:45,865 --> 00:33:47,133
Dragging everyone into it!

560
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:48,334
Ma'am, that's enough.

561
00:33:48,835 --> 00:33:50,236
Ms. Kokonoe.

562
00:33:50,303 --> 00:33:53,039
-I'm sure everyone's exhausted.
-No!

563
00:33:53,106 --> 00:33:55,742
Let's pick this back up at school.

564
00:33:58,511 --> 00:34:00,447
-I'm glad they're okay.
-Thank you.

565
00:34:17,163 --> 00:34:19,733
I'm very sorry.

566
00:34:20,633 --> 00:34:24,037
-I was in Tokyo for--
-The matter's settled.

567
00:34:24,104 --> 00:34:25,472
I will see you tomorrow.

568
00:34:37,183 --> 00:34:39,018
So bright.

569
00:34:41,554 --> 00:34:42,822
Shotaro.

570
00:34:44,290 --> 00:34:45,125
Hey.

571
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:46,826
Hey.

572
00:34:54,201 --> 00:34:55,469
Ms. Suenaga.

573
00:34:56,270 --> 00:34:57,304
Is this…?

574
00:34:59,073 --> 00:35:00,074
Your…?

575
00:35:01,575 --> 00:35:02,676
Yes.

576
00:35:02,743 --> 00:35:04,211
Are you getting married?

577
00:35:04,879 --> 00:35:05,713
Yes.

578
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:07,615
Is that so?

579
00:35:07,681 --> 00:35:10,851
I'm so sorry for dragging
you out for this.

580
00:35:11,519 --> 00:35:13,587
And your fiancé as well.

581
00:35:15,456 --> 00:35:16,290
Akira.

582
00:35:16,824 --> 00:35:18,058
Say you're sorry.

583
00:35:18,893 --> 00:35:19,860
Akira.

584
00:35:19,927 --> 00:35:21,095
It's--

585
00:35:21,162 --> 00:35:23,664
That's why you don't care at all.

586
00:35:25,633 --> 00:35:27,001
What?

587
00:35:27,067 --> 00:35:31,138
Instead of checking on us,
you went straight to our parents.

588
00:35:31,205 --> 00:35:32,406
Worried about your job.

589
00:35:32,473 --> 00:35:34,475
-I didn't mean--
-Akira.

590
00:35:34,542 --> 00:35:37,211
You're just here until you
get married anyway.

591
00:35:37,778 --> 00:35:40,381
You might as well quit now.

592
00:35:44,985 --> 00:35:46,353
What is with your attitude!

593
00:35:47,021 --> 00:35:47,855
Listen up!

594
00:35:48,422 --> 00:35:52,359
I will not tolerate you disrespecting
your teacher this way!

595
00:35:52,426 --> 00:35:53,360
Got it?

596
00:35:53,427 --> 00:35:54,428
I'm okay.

597
00:35:54,495 --> 00:35:55,629
I'm serious.

598
00:35:56,197 --> 00:35:57,431
I'm okay.

599
00:36:02,803 --> 00:36:03,704
Get in.

600
00:36:23,824 --> 00:36:24,959
Kuroiwa.

601
00:36:25,025 --> 00:36:26,160
I'll see you in school.

602
00:36:44,912 --> 00:36:46,113
What's up?

603
00:36:46,180 --> 00:36:47,381
It's my essay.

604
00:36:47,915 --> 00:36:49,617
I submitted it when I applied.

605
00:36:52,353 --> 00:36:54,021
"I want to be depended on.

606
00:36:55,556 --> 00:36:57,892
To notice my student's struggles,

607
00:36:59,927 --> 00:37:01,161
and approach them."

608
00:37:01,729 --> 00:37:05,232
But in reality, I'm useless.

609
00:37:05,299 --> 00:37:06,433
Why?

610
00:37:11,538 --> 00:37:12,773
He's right.

611
00:37:13,574 --> 00:37:15,542
I'm just playing teacher.

612
00:37:20,014 --> 00:37:21,148
Come to Osaka.

613
00:37:23,484 --> 00:37:26,353
Then I'd always be around to listen.

614
00:37:27,554 --> 00:37:29,156
And help anyway I can.

615
00:37:33,827 --> 00:37:34,828
Let's live together.

616
00:37:48,575 --> 00:37:50,678
After your father left,

617
00:37:52,980 --> 00:37:54,748
it was just you and me.

618
00:37:57,518 --> 00:37:58,652
But it was okay,

619
00:37:59,486 --> 00:38:01,522
I was confident we could make it.

620
00:38:04,124 --> 00:38:05,626
You're me.

621
00:38:06,994 --> 00:38:08,595
You're a part of me.

622
00:38:09,129 --> 00:38:12,900
So I knew what you're thinking,
what you're feeling

623
00:38:14,001 --> 00:38:15,869
because we're connected.

624
00:38:18,973 --> 00:38:19,940
But now,

625
00:38:23,010 --> 00:38:25,079
I have no idea anymore.

626
00:38:28,716 --> 00:38:30,217
I don't understand you.

627
00:38:36,991 --> 00:38:38,092
How could you?

628
00:38:40,394 --> 00:38:41,228
Lately,

629
00:38:42,896 --> 00:38:43,964
it's been weird.

630
00:38:48,268 --> 00:38:51,138
I don't even understand myself.

631
00:39:05,419 --> 00:39:06,353
Thanks for cooking.

632
00:39:49,229 --> 00:39:53,734
Even teachers need a break.

633
00:39:53,801 --> 00:39:58,072
You couldn't come right away
during an emergency,

634
00:39:58,138 --> 00:40:00,007
it happens.

635
00:40:00,574 --> 00:40:05,779
Mr. Irie and I covered for you,
and everything worked out!

636
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:07,347
However,

637
00:40:08,248 --> 00:40:09,817
if it were me,

638
00:40:09,883 --> 00:40:14,421
I wouldn't lose my login information
on my first day of school,

639
00:40:14,488 --> 00:40:18,759
I wouldn't stray that far from school even
on the weekends or drink alcohol,

640
00:40:18,826 --> 00:40:23,263
let alone show up
with my lover driving me.

641
00:40:23,330 --> 00:40:26,467
Absolutely unthinkable.

642
00:40:28,102 --> 00:40:31,839
That's because the students
are watching us.

643
00:40:33,774 --> 00:40:36,677
You've lost their trust.

644
00:40:39,313 --> 00:40:40,147
Yes.

645
00:40:41,014 --> 00:40:41,982
I'm sorry.

646
00:40:42,049 --> 00:40:45,752
I suppose, they may call me a relic,

647
00:40:45,819 --> 00:40:48,322
someone stuck in the past.

648
00:40:48,388 --> 00:40:49,256
Not at all.

649
00:40:51,859 --> 00:40:54,495
But I have my conviction.

650
00:40:55,129 --> 00:40:56,897
Teaching is a sacred job.

651
00:40:56,964 --> 00:40:59,466
We must always lead by example.

652
00:40:59,533 --> 00:41:01,001
That is a teacher.

653
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:05,205
No amount of attention is ever enough.

654
00:41:05,272 --> 00:41:07,674
Middle schoolers are precarious creatures.

655
00:41:25,926 --> 00:41:27,761
I've had it.

656
00:41:35,736 --> 00:41:38,272
You should be able to go back
to school tomorrow.

657
00:41:38,338 --> 00:41:41,909
Make sure to apologize to your teachers.

658
00:41:42,876 --> 00:41:44,111
Are you listening?

659
00:41:52,252 --> 00:41:53,187
Hey!

660
00:41:53,253 --> 00:41:55,055
-Don't touch--
-It's from Dad.

661
00:41:55,122 --> 00:41:56,823
Stop! Give that here!

662
00:41:56,890 --> 00:41:59,326
You don't need to read it!

663
00:42:01,028 --> 00:42:02,462
It's complicated.

664
00:42:02,529 --> 00:42:03,997
You're still a child.

665
00:42:05,032 --> 00:42:06,333
You can't understand.

666
00:42:07,801 --> 00:42:09,169
I'm not a kid!

667
00:42:21,682 --> 00:42:22,783
Hello.

668
00:42:23,517 --> 00:42:24,618
Ms. Suenaga.

669
00:42:24,685 --> 00:42:27,354
I came to check on your son
since he wasn't at school.

670
00:42:28,088 --> 00:42:29,156
<i>Well…</i>

671
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:41,034
Sorry.

672
00:42:41,101 --> 00:42:43,237
-Have you seen Kuroiwa?
-Kuroiwa.

673
00:42:43,303 --> 00:42:45,939
<i>No amount of attention is ever enough.</i>

674
00:42:46,506 --> 00:42:48,775
<i>Middle schoolers are precarious creatures.</i>

675
00:43:08,929 --> 00:43:09,963
Kuroiwa!

676
00:43:16,669 --> 00:43:17,570
Kawai.

677
00:43:19,772 --> 00:43:20,973
Ms. Haraguchi!

678
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:22,208
Why are…?

679
00:43:22,275 --> 00:43:23,976
I was going to cook dinner.

680
00:43:24,043 --> 00:43:25,311
What?

681
00:43:25,378 --> 00:43:26,746
Sometimes I want to eat in.

682
00:43:26,812 --> 00:43:28,848
A home cooked meal?

683
00:43:28,914 --> 00:43:30,983
My place is way too tidy to relax.

684
00:43:31,517 --> 00:43:32,718
You already unpacked?

685
00:43:33,286 --> 00:43:35,154
My place is full of boxes.

686
00:43:36,055 --> 00:43:36,889
Push it.

687
00:43:39,358 --> 00:43:42,161
Do we live in the same building?

688
00:43:42,762 --> 00:43:45,598
Our company has a contract
with this building.

689
00:43:46,132 --> 00:43:47,700
So we're neighbors.

690
00:43:50,603 --> 00:43:51,537
What?

691
00:43:53,306 --> 00:43:55,908
You really are so mysterious.

692
00:43:56,475 --> 00:43:58,811
-Am I?
-I thought you were a capable boss.

693
00:43:58,878 --> 00:44:01,480
-Then a mistress?
-With a girlfriend.

694
00:44:02,048 --> 00:44:03,182
I'm bi.

695
00:44:03,249 --> 00:44:04,784
Just so you know.

696
00:44:07,186 --> 00:44:11,824
You're like an onion with so many layers.

697
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:16,829
How's your girlfriend?

698
00:44:17,430 --> 00:44:18,497
She's good.

699
00:44:21,067 --> 00:44:22,068
Kuroiwa!

700
00:44:27,773 --> 00:44:29,108
What are you doing?

701
00:44:29,608 --> 00:44:30,676
Why are you here?

702
00:44:46,726 --> 00:44:47,727
Mayugahama.

703
00:44:48,294 --> 00:44:49,061
What?

704
00:44:49,128 --> 00:44:51,030
I'm going to Mayugahama beach.

705
00:44:54,767 --> 00:44:55,968
It's over 20 kilometers.

706
00:44:57,503 --> 00:44:59,071
I thought I could make it.

707
00:45:00,039 --> 00:45:01,941
It's only half a marathon.

708
00:45:04,276 --> 00:45:05,911
Your mom's worried.

709
00:45:10,850 --> 00:45:11,884
I'll give you a ride.

710
00:45:13,052 --> 00:45:13,886
So get in.

711
00:45:15,020 --> 00:45:16,589
Yes, I just ran into him.

712
00:45:17,123 --> 00:45:18,124
See you soon.

713
00:45:29,335 --> 00:45:31,670
Hold on, I'll find a towel or something.

714
00:45:50,222 --> 00:45:51,490
Anyway,

715
00:45:51,557 --> 00:45:55,060
you're such a guy for trying to
go to the beach.

716
00:45:57,563 --> 00:45:58,964
Always surprising me,

717
00:46:00,032 --> 00:46:01,767
being so unpredictable,

718
00:46:02,334 --> 00:46:03,369
I just don't get it.

719
00:46:14,847 --> 00:46:17,917
<i>Welcome Rain on a Spring Night.</i>

720
00:46:20,386 --> 00:46:22,455
"The good rain knows its season,

721
00:46:24,657 --> 00:46:27,827
When spring arrives, it brings life."

722
00:46:29,161 --> 00:46:30,062
Good rain

723
00:46:32,264 --> 00:46:34,600
chooses when to rain.

724
00:46:35,734 --> 00:46:39,038
It always rains when spring comes.

725
00:46:46,345 --> 00:46:47,947
"It follows the wind

726
00:46:51,884 --> 00:46:53,819
secretly into the night."

727
00:46:54,653 --> 00:46:58,424
It continues to rain through
the night as the wind blows.

728
00:46:59,925 --> 00:47:04,029
"And moistens all things softly,
without sound."

729
00:47:04,830 --> 00:47:08,267
Quietly, while barely making a sound,

730
00:47:09,068 --> 00:47:11,704
it moistens everything.

731
00:47:13,873 --> 00:47:14,707
It's true.

732
00:47:15,608 --> 00:47:16,976
It's just as you said.

733
00:47:18,010 --> 00:47:19,678
I can see the scenery.

734
00:47:34,393 --> 00:47:35,227
I…

735
00:47:38,030 --> 00:47:39,899
I love this poem.

736
00:47:43,669 --> 00:47:45,437
The wind and rain I feel,

737
00:47:48,040 --> 00:47:49,174
the scenery I see,

738
00:47:56,448 --> 00:47:58,617
I always wanted to share it with someone.

739
00:48:02,755 --> 00:48:03,589
Thank you.

740
00:48:08,894 --> 00:48:09,762
Ms. Suenaga.

741
00:48:12,097 --> 00:48:12,965
You won't quit?

742
00:48:16,835 --> 00:48:19,705
Maybe I got my own class too soon.

743
00:48:22,007 --> 00:48:24,977
I mean, it's too late now.

744
00:48:42,528 --> 00:48:43,829
Seatbelt please.

745
00:49:22,201 --> 00:49:23,469
-Yes?
<i>-Hijiri?</i>

746
00:49:24,136 --> 00:49:29,174
Sorry, I had a student runaway,
and I'm taking them home now.

747
00:49:30,042 --> 00:49:33,979
See. Look at you being a good teacher.

748
00:49:37,950 --> 00:49:39,318
I'll call you back.

749
00:49:42,988 --> 00:49:44,089
Let's get you home.

750
00:49:51,530 --> 00:49:52,598
Kuroiwa!

751
00:50:01,173 --> 00:50:02,041
Child.

752
00:50:02,641 --> 00:50:03,942
Student.

753
00:50:08,514 --> 00:50:09,682
I see.

754
00:50:10,215 --> 00:50:11,050
He's home.

755
00:50:11,650 --> 00:50:12,484
Yes.

756
00:50:13,118 --> 00:50:14,620
I'm glad he's okay.

757
00:50:15,754 --> 00:50:16,588
Yes.

758
00:50:17,523 --> 00:50:20,125
Yes, goodbye.

759
00:50:24,129 --> 00:50:25,297
KOSUKE SHIMAZAKI

760
00:50:32,104 --> 00:50:34,239
You're not going to tell Akira about it?

761
00:50:34,306 --> 00:50:35,307
I can't.

762
00:50:37,309 --> 00:50:38,811
How could I?

763
00:50:43,749 --> 00:50:46,685
LESSON PLAN

764
00:50:58,764 --> 00:51:00,733
KOBOSHI JUNIOR HIGH RUMORS

765
00:51:07,473 --> 00:51:09,007
HIJIRI IS GETTING MARRIED NEXT YEAR.

766
00:51:09,074 --> 00:51:10,309
WILY

767
00:51:12,044 --> 00:51:13,579
SNITCH

768
00:51:14,546 --> 00:51:16,381
HER FIANCE WORKS AT A MAJOR COMPANY.

769
00:51:17,116 --> 00:51:18,617
GOLD DIGGER

770
00:51:21,320 --> 00:51:22,354
ANNOYING

771
00:51:22,421 --> 00:51:24,490
QUIT SCHOOL LOL

772
00:51:27,426 --> 00:51:29,027
Don't go, Hijiri!

773
00:51:29,094 --> 00:51:31,964
Snitching is the worst!

774
00:51:32,030 --> 00:51:33,232
So annoying.

775
00:51:34,366 --> 00:51:35,834
Good morning.

776
00:51:37,102 --> 00:51:39,571
-Shut up!
-She's coming!

777
00:51:39,638 --> 00:51:40,839
She's coming!

778
00:51:40,906 --> 00:51:42,374
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

779
00:51:42,441 --> 00:51:46,545
She's here! Come on, she's here!

780
00:51:46,612 --> 00:51:49,114
-She's here.
-Good morning.

781
00:51:52,251 --> 00:51:54,553
CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR WEDDING

782
00:51:57,523 --> 00:51:58,791
I didn't do anything.

783
00:52:00,359 --> 00:52:01,894
She should just quit.

784
00:52:04,396 --> 00:52:07,599
-I was just warning them.
-She's not built for teaching.

785
00:52:07,666 --> 00:52:09,001
I warned them.

786
00:52:09,067 --> 00:52:11,236
Bye, Ms. Suenaga.

787
00:52:29,922 --> 00:52:30,889
I'm not quitting.

788
00:52:38,697 --> 00:52:39,865
I will not quit.

789
00:52:42,234 --> 00:52:44,903
I understand getting disrespected.

790
00:52:45,637 --> 00:52:49,007
My appearance, my lack
of experience and abilities,

791
00:52:49,074 --> 00:52:51,076
I get it more than anyone.

792
00:52:53,078 --> 00:52:55,047
Yes, I have a fiancé.

793
00:52:55,814 --> 00:52:58,250
To be honest, he's wonderful.

794
00:52:58,317 --> 00:52:59,751
I don't deserve him.

795
00:53:01,620 --> 00:53:05,624
My friends ask me if I hypnotized him.

796
00:53:08,493 --> 00:53:09,394
But

797
00:53:11,997 --> 00:53:13,832
I left him behind to be here.

798
00:53:13,899 --> 00:53:15,868
I came because I wanted to see you.

799
00:53:17,569 --> 00:53:18,437
So

800
00:53:20,772 --> 00:53:22,341
I will stay by your side.

801
00:53:23,408 --> 00:53:25,010
One day I'll become a teacher

802
00:53:26,511 --> 00:53:27,613
you can depend on.

803
00:53:47,866 --> 00:53:49,401
I'm starting class.

804
00:53:50,669 --> 00:53:51,703
Open your books to…

805
00:53:51,770 --> 00:53:53,138
<i>So your girlfriend?</i>

806
00:53:53,205 --> 00:53:55,474
She wants to stay at her school for now.

807
00:53:56,041 --> 00:53:58,110
She'll be teaching a while longer.

808
00:53:58,176 --> 00:53:59,177
Good night.

809
00:53:59,678 --> 00:54:01,113
I'm impressed.

810
00:54:01,179 --> 00:54:04,383
She seems normal, but she's not.

811
00:54:04,449 --> 00:54:09,187
She looks like she wouldn't be interested
in something open, but maybe not.

812
00:54:09,254 --> 00:54:10,289
Want to come by?

813
00:54:10,355 --> 00:54:11,156
What?

814
00:54:11,223 --> 00:54:12,691
Want to eat at my place?

815
00:54:12,758 --> 00:54:15,227
I have some pickled onions.

816
00:54:15,994 --> 00:54:16,828
Um,

817
00:54:17,963 --> 00:54:19,431
is this an invitation?

818
00:54:19,498 --> 00:54:21,600
